{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing","doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/IndexedValue"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"let"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"index"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/VectorIndex","text":"VectorIndex","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing11VectorIndexO"}]}],"kind":"declarations"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/IndexedValue\/index","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The index within the vector type to assign the "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to."}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"VHDLParsing"}],"externalID":"s:11VHDLParsing12IndexedValueV5indexAA11VectorIndexOvp","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"let"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"index"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing11VectorIndexO","text":"VectorIndex"}],"title":"index","symbolKind":"property"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/vhdlparsing\/indexedvalue\/index"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://VHDLParsing/documentation/VHDLParsing/IndexedValue":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/IndexedValue","abstract":[{"text":"This type represents a value for a specific index in a vector type within ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VHDL"},{"text":". For example, consider a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"signal ","type":"text"},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with type ","type":"text"},{"code":"std_logic_vector(3 downto 0)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". We can assign specific bits within ","type":"text"},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" by using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"VHDL","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" statement ","type":"text"},{"code":"x <= (3 => '1', others => '0');","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This statement says bit 3 of ","type":"text"},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" should be set to 1","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and all other bits to be set to 0. This type can be used to represent both expressions ","type":"text"},{"code":"3 => '1'","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"others => '0'","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as two separate instances of this type.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"IndexedValue","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IndexedValue","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlparsing\/indexedvalue","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"IndexedValue","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://VHDLParsing/documentation/VHDLParsing":{"title":"VHDLParsing","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/vhdlparsing","role":"collection","abstract":[],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://VHDLParsing/documentation/VHDLParsing/IndexedValue/index":{"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlparsing\/indexedvalue\/index","role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"index","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/IndexedValue\/index","abstract":[{"text":"The index within the vector type to assign the ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"index","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing11VectorIndexO","text":"VectorIndex","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://VHDLParsing/documentation/VHDLParsing/VectorIndex":{"role":"symbol","title":"VectorIndex","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VectorIndex","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLParsing\/documentation\/VHDLParsing\/VectorIndex","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VectorIndex","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlparsing\/vectorindex","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An index of a vector in "},{"code":"VHDL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This type is designed to represent indexes in an assignment statement for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a vector type. For example, you may have a signal "},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" of type "},{"code":"std_logic_vector(7 downto 0)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to assign a value to. In "},{"code":"VHDL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you can do this with the statement "},{"code":"x <= (others => '0');","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This type is designed to represent the "},{"code":"others","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in that statement and other supported values like it, such"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as those found in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x <= (7 => '1', others => '0');"},{"text":". This statement would produce two instances of this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type for the values ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"7"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"others"},{"text":". This type also supports ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VHDL2008"},{"text":" statements that support a range","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of values, e.g. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x <= (7 downto 0 => '1');"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}}}